        h1 Demystifying Buzzwords

      section
        h2 Tech + Data =<br>Buzzword Extravaganza
        a(href="http://blog.stephenwolfram.com/2018/04/buzzword-convergence-making-sense-of-quantum-neural-blockchain-ai/")
          img(src="img/quantum-neural-blockchain-ai.png")

        aside.notes: ul
          li Tech and data are full of buzzwords
          li Buzzwords come and go, and sometime make comebacks
          li This talk covers four buzzwords/phrases

      section
        section
          h1 #1: Big Data

        section
          h2 Big Data: An Enterprise Term
          a(href="https://medium.com/@wtrsld/big-data-made-me-do-it-5bfc3f46871c")
            img(src="img/big-data-enterprise.png")

          aside.notes: ul
            li Big Data has become less trendy in recent years
            li General: Silicon Valley &rarr; population &rarr; corporate world
            li Big Data: outdated to us, still a thing in bigger/slower companies

        section
          h2 Big Data Knows All
          a(href="href=http://dilbert.com/strips/comic/2012-07-29/")
            img.pad-white(src="img/dilbert-big-data.jpg")

          aside.notes: ul
            li This comic captures the spirit of big data
            li Read out comic
            li Not an exaggeration &ndash; CBA as an example

        section
          h2 Big Data... or just a Small Box?
          a(href="https://giphy.com/gifs/afvpets-cats-pets-afv-3oEdv889IaMYigqgZa")
            img(src="img/big-data-small-box.gif")

          aside.notes: ul
            li Is Big Data really a thing?
            li A gigabyte thirty years ago versus today
            li Many valuable datasets are small enough to fit on a beefy server
            li Better to get more computing power before investing in exotic techniques

      section
        section
          h1 #2: Data Science

        section
          h2 Data Science: 2012 Edition

          img(src="img/data-scientist-definition.png")

          img(src="img/data-skill-continuum.png")

          aside.notes: ul
            li Close to my heart &ndash; data scientist since 2012
            li Meaning shifted over time
            li Intersection of software engineering and statistics was six years ago

        section
          h2 Data Science: Too Exclusive?

          a(href="https://datascience.stackexchange.com/a/2406")
            img(src="img/data-scientist-venn-diagram-example.png")

          aside.notes: ul
            li Intersection-based definitions led to many Venn diagrams like this one
            li Data scientist as a unicorn
            li Many people joined the field, leading to a more inclusive definition

        section
          h2 Data Science: 2018 Edition
          blockquote.
            ...we can define data science as a field that deals with description, prediction, and causal inference from
            data in a manner that is both domain-independent and domain-aware, with the ultimate goal of supporting
            decisions.

          .img-source-caption.
            - Yanir Seroussi,
            <a href="https://yanirseroussi.com/2018/07/22/defining-data-science-in-2018/">Defining Data Science in 2018</a>

          aside.notes: ul
            li Definition based on a few sources
            li Read it out

      section
        section
          h1 #3: Artificial Intelligence

          aside.notes: ul
            li One of the hottest terms!

        section
          h2 AI: More Venn Diagram Fun?

          a(href="https://www.kdnuggets.com/2016/03/data-science-puzzle-explained.html")
            img(src="img/ai-data-science-diagram.jpg")

          aside.notes: ul
            li Data loves Venn
            li Not attractive, but captures important intersections
            li AI doesn't mean much, as intelligence isn't well-defined
            li Calculators are intelligent
            li Google search is AI
            li AI: Anything that computers can't do yet?

        section
          h2 AI: The Hype Won't Die

          a(href="https://www.slideshare.net/melsb/intelligence-augmentation-the-nextgen-ai")
            img(src="img/ai-hype-cycle.jpg")

          aside.notes: ul
            li Long history with ups and downs through the years
            li 1950s: decade or two to AGI? Followed by disappointment
            li We're definitely going up these days

        section
          h2 AI and I (2004-2018)

          img(src="img/what-would-you-say-you-do-here.jpg")

          aside.notes: ul
            li Bachelor's from 2004 include AI course and project
            li PhD application in 2008: Something in AI?
            li Graduation 2012: AI experts are silly? Data scientists are sexier
            li Today: AI expert is better?
            li Doesn't matter in terms of substance, but branding is important

      section
        section
          h1 #4: Machine Learning

        section
          h2 Machine Learning by Example

          a(href="https://www.xenonstack.com/blog/data-science/log-analytics-deep-machine-learning-ai/")
            img.pad-white(src="img/machine-learning-vs-deep-learning.png")

          aside.notes: ul
            li Broadly: Pattern extraction
            li Data: Images tagged as car/not-car
            li Traditional: Data scientist to generate features
            li ML algorithm: Extract patterns
            li New image: car/not-car
            li DL: Reduce need for manual work to generate features for some problems

        section
          h2 ML: A Solved Problem?

          a(href="http://www.shivonzilis.com/machineintelligence")
            img(src="img/machine-intelligence-landscape-core-technologies.png")

          img(src="img/ben-hamner-black-box-ml.png")

          aside.notes: ul
            li Solved problem given cloud-based services and libraries?
            li Yes, that's why don't talk about algorithms much
            li Defining problems and collecting the right data are more important and hard than ML

        section
          h2 Machine Learning Map

          a(href="http://scikit-learn.org/stable/tutorial/machine_learning_map/index.html")
            img(src="img/scikit-learn-map.png")

          aside.notes: ul
            li Need some knowledge to decided what ML method to apply
            li To be discussed later

        section
          h2 Machine Learning Pipeline

          a(href="https://www.infoworld.com/article/3198252/machine-learning/data-in-intelligence-out-machine-learning-pipelines-demystified.html")
            img(src="img/machine-learning-pipeline.jpg")

          aside.notes: ul
            li ML model isn't enough
            li Usefulness isn't covered by ML
            li Shipping to production has many parts
            li To be discussed later

      section
        h1 Questions?

